rca_of_the_issue.mitigation:
Modify api.js 401 handler to check current path or use a whitelist. Example fix:
```javascript
if (error.response?.status === 401) {
  const path = window.location.pathname;
  const openAccessPaths = ['/app/story-video-studio', '/app/story-preview'];
  if (!openAccessPaths.some(p => path.startsWith(p))) {
    localStorage.removeItem('token');
    window.location.href = '/login';
  }
}
```
